            <div type="translation">
                <p>O Pantanassa, and all-[surpassing chaste lady and mother of the Lord, see the desire of my miserable] soul and become my intercessor in the hour of judgment that I may be spared the lot of [...Nikephoros] magistros, of the (family of the) Ischyrioi. (<ptr target="#Ševčenko2012"/>, 77)</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The proposed reconstitution of the inscription is based on a comparison with the similar inscription at the base of the conch of the roughly contemporary church of the Panagia at Trikomo <!-- add here the link to the Trikomo inscription? -->, the painted decoration of which is ascribed by scholars to members of the same workshop as that of Asinou (<ptr target="#Ševčenko2012"/>, 77, 79). At some later date, the inscription was plastered over and recopied (white letters on blue background), but this later layer has now been removed.</p>
            </div>
